SYNTAX: <opcode><args>; opcode is integer, args comma-separated

OPCODES

2 VAR 2<name,value> declare & assign
3 SET 3<name,value> update variable
4 GLOBAL 4<name> mark global in function
16 FUNCTION 16<name|body> define function
17 CALL 17<name,arg1,arg2...> call function

18 RET 18<value> return from function
32 FOR 32<I,start,end,step|body> loop (end exclusive)
33 WHILE 33<condition|body> while loop
34 BREAK 34<label> break from loop
48 ARRAY 2<ARR,48<v1,v2,v3>> array (expression-only)

49 IN 2<FOUND,49<val,ARR>> membership (expression-only)
50 INDEX 50<ARR,idx,DEST> get element

51 SET_IDX 51<ARR,idx,val> set element
64 ADD 64<A,B,DEST> A+B→DEST
65 SUB 65<A,B,DEST> A-B→DEST
66 MUL 66<A,B,DEST> A*B→DEST
67 DIV 67<A,B,DEST> A/B→DEST
68 MOD 68<A,B,DEST> A%B→DEST
80 EQ 80<A,B> A==B
81 NE 81<A,B> A!=B
82 GT 82<A,B> A>B

83 LT 83<A,B> A<B
84 GTE 84<A,B> A>=B
85 LTE 85<A,B> A<=B
96 AND 96<c1,c2> c1&&c2
97 OR 97<c1,c2> c1||c2
98 NOT 98<c> !c
112 IF 112<condition|body> if
113 ELIF 113<condition|body> elif
114 ELSE 114|body else (no condition)
128 LABEL 128<label> label
129 GOTO_IF 129<cond,label> conditional goto

144 GOTO 144<label> goto
192 WRITE 192~WRITELN<val> print+newline
208 STRING 208~METHOD<args,DEST> string ops
224 MATH 224~METHOD<args,DEST> math ops
STRING METHODS
FIND 208~FIND<string,substring,DEST>
LEN 208~LEN<string,DEST>
UPPER 208~UPPER<string,DEST>
LOWER 208~LOWER<string,DEST>
SLICE 208~SLICE<string,start,end,DEST>
CONCAT 208~CONCAT<str1,str2,DEST>
REPLACE 208~REPLACE<string,old,new,DEST>
MATH METHODS
POW 224~POW<base,exp,DEST>
SQRT 224~SQRT<num,DEST>
ABS 224~ABS<num,DEST>
MIN 224~MIN<a,b,DEST>
MAX 224~MAX<a,b,DEST>
FLOOR 224~FLOOR<num,DEST>
CEIL 224~CEIL<num,DEST>
ROUND 224~ROUND<num,DEST>
LITERALS
$N integer: $42, $100, $0
@N.M float: @3.14, @2.5
"text" string: "hello"
\" escape: \"quote\"

RULES

1. DEST in arithmetic/string/math must pre-exist: 2<Z,0>;64<X,Y,Z>
2. Opcodes 48,49 expression-only: 2<ARR,48<1,2,3>>
3. Loop variables pre-declare: 2<SUM,0>;32<I,1,11,1|64<SUM,I,SUM>>
4. Chain ELIF/ELSE before IF: 113<...>; 112<...> or 114|...; 112<...>
5. ELSE uses 114|body (no condition, no < >)
TEST CASES (format: code: output)
1. 192~WRITELN<"Hello, World!">: Hello, World!

2. 2<X,10>;192~WRITELN<X>: 10
3. 2<X,10>;3<X,20>;192~WRITELN<X>: 20
4. 32<I,0,5,1|192~WRITELN<I>>: 0\n1\n2\n3\n4
5. 2<R,0>;224~POW<2,10,R>;192~WRITELN<R>: 1024
6. 2<STR,"hello">;2<UP,"">;208~UPPER<STR,UP>;192~WRITELN<UP>: HELLO
7. 2<RESULT,0>;16<ADD_ONE,N|2<R,0>;64<N,1,R>;18<R>>;192~WRITELN<17<ADD_ONE,5,RESULT>>: 6
8. 2<n,5>;16<inc_n|4<n>;64<n,1,n>>;17<inc_n>;192~WRITELN<n>: 6
9. 16<SUM3,A,B,C|2<T,0>;2<R,0>;64<A,B,T>;64<T,C,R>;18<R>>;192~WRITELN<17<SUM3,10,20,30,OUT>>: 60
10. 2<n,1>;112<80<n,0>|65<n,1,n>>;113<80<n,1>|65<n,2,n>>;113<80<n,2>|65<n,3,n>>;114|192~WRITELN<"n must be 0-2">;192~WRITELN<n>: -1
11. 2<SUM,0>;32<I,1,11,1|64<SUM,I,SUM>>;192~WRITELN<SUM>: 55
12. 2<STR,"strawberry">;2<COUNT,0>;2<LEN,0>;2<CH,"">;2<NEXT,0>;208~LEN<STR,LEN>;32<I,0,LEN,1|64<I,1,NEXT>;208~SLICE<STR,I,NEXT,CH>;112<80<CH,"r">|64<COUNT,1,COUNT>>>;192~WRITELN<COUNT>: 3

